responsible for the Nice group, and Salvatore Bonanno. Pietro Alfio Cosentino, recipient of the precautionary custody in prison and referent of the Mafia clan Santapaola-Ercolano in Tremestieri Etneo, would have used to guarantee the respect of precise electoral agreements propedeutic to the election of the current mayor of Tremestieri Etneo, Rando, in prison for political-mafia electoral exchange and aggravated corruption, in relation to the 31 elections
&nbsp;
However, after the election victory of the Rando, a series of judicial operations (and in particular those called "Kronos" and "Carthago2") certified membership of our Catanian Church of Francesco Santapaola and Vito Romeo, involving Alfio Romeo; judicial events that were, in the eyes of those who had benefited from electoral support, an uncompromising prejudice for the fulfillment of the promises, which would only therefore be concrete This is followed by the strong discontent expressed by the family of Romeo, excluded from any direct use despite the electoral support provided, while Cosentino, after obtaining the work of the two sons, was excluded from the electoral lists for the administrative elections of 2021, as it became a subject easily reconnected to the Santapaola-Ercolano.<br> <br> THE DEPUTATO. AGREEMENTS, CIMICI In this context, elements were acquired that would demonstrate, for the magistrates, "a business degeneration of the local government of the municipality of Tremestieri Etneo", of which Luca Sammartino, at the time of the regional de facto, was the main political representative of the first citizen Santi Rando. Regarding the League's exponent, "the concern of the League to take shelter from any investigation activity in place against it, excluding from the lists the subjects in the smell of organized crime, of which it seems to have been used during the elections". It would also be activated "to put in place activities of vigilance and technical remediation of the premises of its political secretariat availing of staff of the Carabinieri in service and in quiescenza, also trying to acquire confidential information about the possible slope to its charge of criminal proceedings". Specifically, Ronsisvalle, owner of a pharmacy in Tremestieri, under house arrest for instigation to corruption, would have been favored by reducing the number of pharmacies present in the municipal organic plant, obtaining in return the promise of electoral support in view of the 2019 European elections for the candidate supported by Sammartino.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
THE 'BONIFICATION' OF CARABINIERE' As part of the same order, the gip has reserved its decision against a military officer of the Arma in active service, "of which Sammartino would be used, behind the co-responsion of sums of money, to perform technical reclamation activities in search of microspies in its offices"; the military plan, therefore, will be subjected to interrogation, after which the gip will evaluate the application of the interdictive measure of the suspension from the exercise of a public office or service, as required by the prosecutor.<br> <br> MAZZETTE mayor, FUNZIONARI E IMPRENDITORI> <br> Numerosi the episodes of corruption in the Municipality of Tremestieri that would have seen in mayor Raccando and Giovanni Among the recipients of the precautionary measure, in fact, there are also four entrepreneurs (one already deceased by natural causes) who emerged in the context of as many shortcomings, in relation to which they would have benefited, in exchange for money and other utilities unlawfully issued to the public officials, of the granting of municipal permits (authorizations to build and change of destination of use) and assignments of public works (restructuring only Elements, for those accused who would seem to outline a strategy of the summits of the municipality of Tremestieri Etneo "to neutralize any form of political opposition", reaching to favor the historical opposition advisor Mario Ronsisvalle.<br> <br> LE MISURE CAUTELARI><br> Custoria cautionre in prison for Pietro Alfio Cosentino, of Trecastagni, 62 years; Santi Rando, Catania, 49 years old. To the house arrests Paolo Di Loreto, Catania, 72 years; Giuseppe Monaco, called "Puccio", of Catania, 72 years; Giovanni Naccarato, born in Naples, 58 years; Mario Ronsisvalle, from Catania, 54 years old. Suspension for the duration of a year by public offices covered and all activities related to Luca Sammartino, Catania, 39 years; Michele Platania, Catania, 56 years old. For a year, it is forbidden to exercise their business activities and to cover the management offices of legal persons for Domenico Cucinotta, Catania, 64 years old; Giuseppe Ferlito, of Catania, 64 years; Mario Stanganelli, from Palagonia, 58.&nbsp;

