AGI - Some members of the student collectives of the University La Sapienza have chained themselves after starting a hunger strike. Students are in garrison with tents within the university. "Appeal to democratic, pacifists and civil society to support the demands of students and academics in universities to stop genocide in Palestine. We are students and students of the University La Sapienza of Rome, we decided to undertake a hunger strike from the morning of Wednesday, April 17th, chained under the rectory of our university", write the university." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"We have come to the choice of this form of non-violent protest, after months of a heterogeneous and widespread mobilization that has seen in different sectors of society a clear stance against wars, for a ceasefire, to stop the ongoing escalation that risks dragging the world into a third world war torn apart", they still write students. "To all this - they continue - but it is only a worrying anti-democratic sight that in the most extreme cases has also been translated into manganelli and repressive violence on students and students, so many the last known events".
&nbsp;
For this reason, university students appeal "to all democratic, pacifist and civil society subjects to support us in these hours and to give resonance to this path that wants to release from any complicity and stop escalation". Finally, a request to the writer Antonella Polimeni because "it urgently summons a moment of wide and open confrontation between all the components of the Athenaeum to force the reasons of those who want the immediate ceasefire and the end of the genocide in Gaza".
&nbsp;

