<div </div
&nbsp;
<
"I heard the Quantum Belfiore to express my thanks to the police forces and my closeness to the wounded agents following the unconscious episodes that took place this afternoon at the Sapienza University of Rome, underlining how the work of law enforcement prevented the event to degenerate with more serious consequences," said the Prefect of Rome, Lamberto Giannini. "Manifesting your ideas is a constitutional right which, in itself, contains the concept of confrontation, which, by its very nature, repudiates all forms of violence to this purpose," the Prefect added.
</div
&nbsp;
According to Domenico Pianese, secretary of the police union Coisp, "the events organized by collectives and social centers have the sole purpose of fomenting and feeding the clashes with the Forces of the Order; These characters who descend into the street and move from protesters, in reality they only seek a way to provoke tension and create chaos." A communiqué arrived in the evening in the drafts and signed by some representatives of the students of the Communist Youth Front: "We have been mobilizing for months and receiving no other response except the repression by the athenaeus. Today we had called for a strike to demand a stance from the athene against the genocide in palestine and the withdrawal of military agreements stipulated by wisdom with military companies and Israeli universities. The answer we received is that of a Rector who only knows the Manganello as a method of managing dialogue with students."
&nbsp;
Violence is never acceptable, from no point of view and in no form - said Giovanna Iannantuoni, President of CRUI - "It is even more inadmissible when trying to force a decision taken democratically by a governing body of a university. Italian universities are and will always be the place of comparison of ideas and culture. Rector Polimeni has all my solidarity."
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;

